The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for skeleton-based action recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different encoding methods and joint selection for feature extraction, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on a large-scale dataset, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the proposed method for human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
